    // If we can calculate $\text{Cost2}(L, X)$ and $\text{Cost2}(Y, R)$ fast, we are good. This means we need Single Source Shortest Path (SSSP) for all $N$ sources in the Type 2 graph, which is $O(N^2)$.

    // Since the structure of the Type 2 graph is simple (max degree 2, locally), perhaps we can use techniques for paths on trees/lines.

